<channel|># 詞: 銀包

1. 我唔記得咗將個銀包擺喺邊，幫我搵下。 (I forgot where I put my wallet; please help me find it.)
2. 佢行街嗰陣唔小心跌咗個銀包。 (He accidentally dropped his wallet while walking down the street.)
3. 我個銀包太舊喇，打算買個新嘅。 (My wallet is too old; I'm planning to buy a new one.)
4. 佢個銀包入面除咗錢，仲有好多相。 (Besides money, there are many photos inside her wallet.)
5. 記得將銀包擺喺袋入面，唔好隨便攞出嚟。 (Remember to keep your wallet in your bag; don't take it out carelessly.)
6. 我啱啱發現我個銀包被偷咗！ (I just discovered that my wallet has been stolen!)
7. 呢個皮質銀包好耐用，用咗五年都冇爛。 (This leather wallet is very durable; it hasn't worn out even after five years of use.)
8. 佢個銀包厚到連個袋都閂唔到。 (His wallet is so thick that he can't even close his bag.)
9. 我喺地鐵站拾到個銀包，已經交咗畀職員。 (I found a wallet at the MTR station and have already handed it over to the staff.)
10. 佢每次出街都習慣將銀包擺喺內袋，咁樣比較安全。 (He habitually keeps his wallet in his inner pocket whenever he goes out, as it's safer.)

完成10句例句 [end of text]


